snippet.title: Blood Parliament - BBC Africa Eye Documentary
snippet.description:
#BBCAfricaEye investigates the shootings of three demonstrators during the Kenya Finance Bill 2024 protest in Nairobi on June 25th.

Click here to subscribe to our channel 👉🏽 http://bit.ly/subscribetoafrica

On June 25th 2024, blood was spilt at Kenya’s parliament.

That day, thousands of protestors headed there to stop the 2024 finance bill being passed into law. En-route they were met with tear gas, truncheons, and even gunfire. When they got there, and stormed the legislature, some of that gunfire turned lethal. At least three people were killed: students, shopkeepers, and Sunday school teachers. Since then, no one has been held to account for their deaths.

Now, using open-source intelligence (OSINT) and forensic techniques, #BBCAfricaEye can expose the men who spilled blood on the grounds of Kenya’s parliament.

00:00 June 25th: Protesting a finance bill, livestreaming a revolution
01:10 “The People’s Assembly, belongs to the people”
03:37 The March to Parliament
04:03 'It's already really hard for everyone - the taxes will make life much harder'
04:50 'It's the working, middle and lower class against the ruling class' 
06:10 The Day Begins: “This is something this country has never seen before”
08:04 Protesters Face Off with Police: “This is Kenya. We are one.”
11:02 Parliament is breached
13:00 David Chege and Ericsson Mutisya are killed ​
21:20 The Second Incursion: Eric Shieni is shot
26:24 Who killed Eric Shieni?
34:20 June 26th: President Ruto withdraws the 2024 Finance Bill
34:50 “You must listen to the heartbeat of the nation”

snippet.title: Walioua vijana bungeni Kenya wafichuliwa
snippet.description:
Mnamo Juni 25, 2024, damu ilimwagika katika Bunge la Kenya.

Siku hiyo, maelfu ya waandamanaji walielekea bungeni ili kusitisha muswada wa fedha #FinanceBill2024 kupitishwa 
kuwa sheria.
Njiani walikutana na mabomu ya machozi, virungu, na hata milio ya risasi.

Walipofika huko, na kulivamia bunge, baadhi ya milio ya risasi hiyo ikageuka kuwa hatari zaidi

Takriban watu watatu waliuawa: mwanafunzi, muuza duka, na mwalimu. 

Tangu wakati huo, hakuna mtu aliyeshikiliwa kuwajibika kwa vifo vyao.

Sasa, #BBCAfricaEye inawafichua walisababisha damu kumwagika nje ya viwanja vya Bunge Kenya.
#bbcswahili #financebill #financebill202 
Subscribe kupata video motomoto kila siku kutoka BBC Idhaa ya Kiswahili https://www.youtube.com/channel/UCoerKKIKIMlDYaVFSTlsWGw

snippet.title: BBC identifies security forces who shot Kenya anti-tax protesters | BBC News
snippet.description:
The members of Kenya's security forces who shot dead anti-tax protesters at the country's parliament in June have been identified by the BBC.
 
The BBC's analysis of more than 5,000 images also shows that those killed there were unarmed and not posing a threat.
 
The East African nation's constitution guarantees the right to peaceful protest, and the deaths caused a public outcry.
 
Despite a parliamentary committee ordering Kenya's Independent Policing Oversight Authority to investigate the deaths on the streets of the capital, Nairobi - and make public its findings - no report regarding the killings at parliament has yet been issued and no-one has been held to account.

Subscribe here: http://bit.ly/1rbfUog

For more news, analysis and features visit: www.bbc.com/news

snippet.title: Watch the highlights of the funeral of Pope Francis
snippet.description:
Catch up on the key moments from the funeral of Pope Francis in Vatican City and the procession to Santa Maria Maggiore in Rome, where he was buried.

0:00 Sealing of the pope's coffin
1:29 Crowds gather in St. Peter's Square. Presidents Donald Trump and Volodymyr Zelensky join the congregation
3:51 Procession out of St. Peter's Basilica with the Pope's coffin
9:23 Cardinal Giovanni Battista Re, Dean of the College of Cardinals, starts the funeral Mass with the Penitential Act
12:07 Kielce Gussie, an American journalist for Vatican News, reads from Acts 10:34-43
13:24 Homily by Cardinal Giovanni Battista Re
16:33 The Communion Rite: The "Our Father"
17:40 Communion is distributed to the congregation
19:37 Representatives of Eastern Catholic churches
22:22 Procession with the coffin back into St. Peter's Basilica
26:15 St. Peter's Basilica bells toll
26:52 Procession to Santa Maria Maggiore in Rome
29:56 Procession arrives at Santa Maria Maggiore

#CNN  #News

snippet.title: Harmonize - Yeye (Official Visualizer)
snippet.description:
“Yeye” Is A Powerful And Vulnerable Expression From Harmonize, Diving Deep Into The Emotional Highs And Lows Of Life From Moments Of Pain, Addiction, And Loneliness, To A Profound Realization Of God’s Unfailing Love. The Swahili Word “Yeye” (Meaning “Him”) Refers To God, Who, In Harmonize’s Words, Remains His Only Constant When Everything Else Falls Apart.

Blending Soulful Bongo Flava With Heartfelt Lyrics, Harmonize Opens Up Like Never Before Sharing How Temporary Pleasures And Human Approval Left Him Feeling Empty, But How Faith And Divine Connection Brought Him Peace And Purpose. Whether Facing Rejection, Debt, Or Even Thoughts Of Death, He Finds Strength In Knowing That God Never Turns Away.

This Track Isn’t Just A Song It’s A Testimony. Honest, Raw, And Beautifully Melodic, “Yeye” Speaks To Anyone Who’s Ever Felt Lost But Held Onto Faith. Harmonize Invites Listeners Into His Personal Journey, Reminding Us That Even In Our Darkest Moments, God’s Love Shines Brightest.

snippet.title: Diamond Platnumz - Kuna (Official Lyric Audio)
snippet.description:
Download The Song👇👇👇
https://dplatnumz.lnk.to/kuna

Diamond Platnumz is back with another infectious hit, "Kuna," a song that brings the raw energy of the coastal Vanga sound into the modern Bongo Flava scene. This track is all about rhythm, vibe, and cheeky storytelling—packed with playful, flirtatious lyrics that will have fans singing along in no time.

With its catchy call-and-response style and irresistible beat, "Kuna" feels like a celebration of Swahili culture and coastal traditions. Diamond’s signature charisma shines through as he blends humor, streetwise wit, and addictive melodies into a song that’s impossible to sit still to.

From the clubs to the streets, "Kuna" is that kind of song that brings people together—whether you’re dancing, laughing, or just vibing to the beat. This one is guaranteed to be on heavy rotation!
